---
permalink: /
pagination:
  include: All
  per_page: 10
  permalink_suffix: "blogposts/{{ num }}.html"
  order: Desc
  sort_by: ["published_date", "title Asc"]
  date_index: ["Year", "Month", "Day"]
---

<section id="intro" class="s-intro target-section">
    <div class="s-intro__bg rellax" data-rellax-speed="-7"></div>

    <div class="row s-intro__content">
        <div class="column">
            <div class="s-intro__content-about">
                <h1>“It compiles! Ship it!”</h1>
                <h3 style="padding-bottom: 0px;">Thoughts and posts about this and that in the world of software architecture and development.</h3>

                <ul style="margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
                    {% for post in paginator.pages %}
                    <li><a href="{{ post.permalink }}">{{ post.title }}</a></li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>

                {% if paginator.previous_index or paginator.next_index %}
                <div class="s-intro__content-social" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
                    {% if paginator.previous_index %}
                    <a href="/{{ paginator.previous_index_permalink }}">
                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </a>
                    {% endif %}
                    {% if paginator.next_index %}
                    <a href="/{{ paginator.next_index_permalink }}">
                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </a>
                    {% endif %}
                </div>
                <br>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="about" class="s-about target-section">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="column large-3 tab-12">
            <img class="s-about__pic" src="images/avatar.jpg" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="column large-9 tab-12 s-about__content">
            <h3>About Me</h3>
            <p>
                Interested in modern software architecture, development and working efficiently in heterogeneous and focused teams.
            </p>
            <p>
                80s kid, music lover and software development passionist based in Dortmund, Germany.
                Started my IT path in school.
                Achieved Bachelor in Information Technology.
                Dropped Master at around 80-90%.
                Life is not about a perfect CV, but passion for what you do.
                Software development.
                Software architecture.
                Is it art or engineering?
                Creativity or hard facts?
                So-called soft skills or frameworks and technologies?
                Keep it balanced.
            </p>
            <p>Feel free to reach me through my profiles.</p>

            {% include "social-links.liquid" %}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="resume" class="s-resume target-section" style="padding-bottom: 0px;">
    <div class="row s-resume__section">
        <div class="column large-3 tab-12">
            <h3 class="section-header-allcaps">Current Training Topics</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="column large-9 tab-12">
            <div class="resume-block">
                <p>
                    With more than 15 years of experience, anyone could create a page-long list of technical capabilities, frameworks, and libraries.
                    I don't think that would be useful.
                    So I'd like to give you some insights into topics that I'm currently trying to learn or improve.
                    Since this is largely done in my spare time, some of these topics may take some time.
                </p>

                <ul class="skill-bars-fat">
                    {% for skill in site.data.learning.skills %}
                    <li>
                        <div class="progress percent{{ skill.percentage }}"></div>
                        <strong>{{ skill.topic }}</strong>
                    </li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>

                <p>To avoid any interpretation as to priority or focus, the topics are in alphabetical order.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
